    "4 afeyJfciJK Jut DEMOCRATIC convention delegate like their GOP predecessors passed pickelline protesting against the TaftHartley act injunctions and Jim Crow in the arme dforcesand demanding FEPC antipoll tax and antilynch legislation THE CHICAGO STAR JULY 24 1948 Trip to New York is prize in Peace Bond contest A free trip to New York will be awarded by the Progressive Party to the person who sells the greatest amount in Peace Bonds by Aug 15 Second prize in the PPls con test to raise funds for its elec tion campaign will be a paid weekend at Charmaine Lodge popular resort on Chain OLakes near Waupaca Wis A fur coat to guard against winters blizzards will be the third prize to be awarded to an individual bond salesman Other lesser prizes will be given to runnersup HENRY A Wallace Presiden tial candidate will speak at spe cial meetings of the three ward clubs that sell the most bonds Ahead in the running in the first group of ward clubs this week was the 22nd ward which went over its quota of S2OO The ward reported sales of 26263 In group two the leader was the 6th ward with sales of S2BO"
